Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.78,0:01:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,thought I would sort of tell you how the day is going to go. We originally\Nallocated two hours for lunch. I think that's too long. Is that sort of boring
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.97,0:01:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,after two hours? I think maybe we'll resume the lecture at 1.30. There's a\Ngroup here from out of state. Are there a bunch of people here from Wisconsin or
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.99,0:01:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that group? Oh, goopoo. I thought the Wisconsin group, I'll meet with them in\Nthe viewing room about 1.15. We'll meet with you especially and then we'll vacate
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.36,0:01:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the viewing room for the others at 1.30 and go on the lecture. But I thought we'd\Nmeet together. You know, I grew up in Wisconsin and I've been back there in a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.78,0:02:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,long time. 60 years, I guess, or something. A long time. Well, the evolution of\Nconsciousness. Do we have, we'll explain how the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.47,0:02:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,arose.\NPeople in spiritual work are concerned with the ego. And in the 400s, people are
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.76,0:02:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,intelligent and well-read. They know that that's their problem, how to transcend\Nthis ego, how to approach the ego. The reason I like the Course in Miracles
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.08,0:02:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,workbook, it calibrates at 600. The text calibrates at 550. The difference is that\NI don't like about the textbook is that it tends to demonize the ego and set up a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.13,0:02:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,duality.\NAnd part of your mind sees the ego as the enemy. I brought my ego with me to show you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.31,0:03:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the true nature of the ego. The ego is troublesome, but it's really a pussycat when you begin\Nto understand what it's about. We have the evolution of consciousness beginning back
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.73,0:03:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in time. If you've got this, on this wonderful machine here, we've got, you know, the evolution\Nof consciousness – we've got paleontology, we've got Epcox.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.43,0:03:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,See life, if you understand the ego, then you begin to – you stop demonizing it.\NI don't know what's going on. Somebody has to tell me half the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.51,0:03:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, there's no life on Mars. To speak the person on Mars, there is notсудy,\NWe knew that with kinesiology before they went there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.56,0:04:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They ain't done that yet.\NAll right, so, Sanyo, oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.07,0:04:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, on this planet, there was no life,\Nand then a life appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.38,0:04:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It appeared, you see, if you were going to establish life\Non a, let's say, hostile, it's not really hostile,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.48,0:04:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but not friendly planet, it's just all rocks and dirt, you know.\NIn the middle of this planet is molten.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.32,0:04:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The center of the Earth, then, is a fireball,\Nwhich over zillions of years, quadrillions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.46,0:04:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,gradually cooled down enough that the surface\Nwas congenial to life circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.23,0:04:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,While it's a fiery ball at a couple thousand degrees Fahrenheit,\Nit's not too friendly to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.47,0:04:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Although life did manage, there is bacteria\Nthat live in the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.01,0:04:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In the center of the earth, in the molten lava.\NSo life is tenacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.03,0:05:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So what would be the first principle and rule of life\Nif it were going to establish itself on this planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.26,0:05:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It would have to be programmed, then,\Nto serve its own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.70,0:05:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The core of the ego, then, is self-serving,\Nbecause without self-servingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.50,0:05:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,no existence is possible.\NLife, then, requires energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.53,0:05:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have enough energy.\NAnd so the essence of life is to get energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.66,0:05:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The amoeba goes out there and gets energy.\NIn the beginning, the first signs of life, bacteria,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.04,0:05:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I got this thing here.\NI'm not used to it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.40,0:05:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, be careful, don't shine it in anybody's eyes.\NI'm a little scared of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.03,0:06:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, this is so far long ago\Nthat I don't even know what those words mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.96,0:06:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If we calibrate what's at this time of the rock age,\Nage of oldest dated rocks,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.18,0:06:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,1, 8, 50, with about 10 zeros after it,\Nago, first signs of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.80,0:06:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,actually, it's below this.\NIt's at 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.73,0:06:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Bacteria are at 1.\NAlgae aren't aware they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.40,0:06:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And viruses are not aware they are.\NVirus just reproduces DNA,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.24,0:06:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but it doesn't know that it is.\NBacteria is the first, it calibrates at 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.81,0:06:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you see the evolution of consciousness\Nthroughout the ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.50,0:06:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You see consciousness gradually.\NScorpions at 17.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.92,0:07:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I know why I never liked scorpions much.\NAnd sharks, you see, shell-crushing sharks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.74,0:07:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you see, life has to evolve.\NSelf-interest, self-interest is the necessity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.24,0:07:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So if it wasn't for the selfishness of life,\Nnone of us would be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.84,0:07:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point in demonizing selfishness.\NIf it wasn't for selfishness, you wouldn't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.40,0:07:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Because life would not have survived.\NIt survives because it's interested in me, that I get.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.70,0:07:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have enough energy, enough molecules,\Nso I'll eat somebody and then I'll have more energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.84,0:07:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So energy acquisition, then, is necessary to life.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.02,0:07:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see, life then evolves.\NAnd birds, you see, primitive mammals, modern mammals.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.73,0:07:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, the evolution of consciousness\Nover great eons of time
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.77,0:08:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is completely and totally self-interested\Nuntil you see the animal kingdom at 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.49,0:08:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We got animal kingdom there?\NAnimal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.39,0:08:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Animal kingdom.\NAnimal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.45,0:08:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Animal kingdom.\NSo the core of your ego better be interested in self-interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.31,0:08:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It better be selfish.\NOtherwise, you won't live long enough to become spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.06,0:08:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, bacteria.\NWe love the protozoas.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.44,0:08:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got a present from my sweet wife.\NShe gave me a, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.80,0:08:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,A trilobite, yes.\NSo we calibrated our trilobite back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.41,0:08:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Our crustacean at three.\NSo my trilobite at home calibrates at three.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.96,0:09:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We get up to six, the fish at 20, sharks.\NYou see how these are all self-interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.07,0:09:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a Komodo dragon.\NCan you believe there's somebody crazy enough
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.95,0:09:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to get into a Komodo dragon's cage with him?\NThat was Neville Chamberlain before World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.73,0:09:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you're nice to the Komodo dragon,\Nhe'll be nice to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.00,0:09:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bin Laden is just misguided.\NAnd if we're nice,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.02,0:09:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,if we're nice to him,\Nhe'll be nice with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.72,0:09:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NSo Komodo dragon bit the guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.99,0:09:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he didn't die,\Nso he had some good karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.66,0:09:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Reptiles at 40.\NAnd then we get to the predatory mammals, snakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.20,0:09:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing about predatory mammals\Nis you can make them pets for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.69,0:09:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,As they get older,\Nthey revert and will kill you,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.84,0:10:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as the lady who raised the lion found out.\NAnd remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.79,0:10:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,some years ago back in maybe the 50s,\Ntheir ocelots were sort of a craze with ocelots.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.53,0:10:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The only trouble was the ocelot got older,\Nhe started to eat your child,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.97,0:10:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so you had to get rid of him.\NSo we find out ocelots don't work
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.23,0:10:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,because their inner nature is the way it is.\NTherefore, freedom is not denial.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.37,0:10:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom is relinquishing denial\Nand seeing it as childish naivete.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.47,0:10:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NThen we see the whales and the dolphins.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.68,0:10:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people cheer for them,\Nsome people cheer for the dolphins.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.64,0:10:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hear it for the dolphins.\NHey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.64,0:10:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Migratory birds, birds of prey,\Nrodents, rhinoceros, songbirds, doves,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.56,0:10:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,polar bears, grizzly bears, water buffalo.\NYou see, a bear is fun, but he'll also kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.64,0:11:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wait long enough,\Nas he gets older,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.64,0:11:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,one day he's going to get pissed.\NHa ha ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.80,0:11:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over for you.\NI'm trying to get people out of spiritual naivete.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.43,0:11:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,People become spiritual,\Nit's hearts and flowers and piety.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.43,0:11:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're deadly.\NThey walk you right over the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.41,0:11:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Walk you right over the cliff.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.41,0:11:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's not discernment.\NDiscernment is the opening of the third eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.70,0:11:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowingness that you just know\Nwhat is integrous and what is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.70,0:11:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Until the third eye of the Buddhic body opens up,\Nyou have to take the word of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.70,0:11:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And kinesiology certainly serves that purpose.\NSo the water buffalo is a renowned killer of humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.40,0:11:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The wolves, the hippopotamus,\Nthe hippopotamus kills more humans
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.47,0:11:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,than any other animal.\NThat's always a strange statistic to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.47,0:12:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are people in the water\Nwith the hippopotamus in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.06,0:12:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't really the alligator.\NThe alligator kills a lot of people too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.06,0:12:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not their fault. It's not the hippopotamus' fault.\NThe hippopotamus isn't enough to get in there with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.06,0:12:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just picked how they're going to leave this planet.\NSome things, some things
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.28,0:12:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,become sanctified.\NVery interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.44,0:12:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We did food before and after it's blessed.\NThe highest quality food,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.80,0:12:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the highest energy is homemade food.\NIt's then blessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.80,0:12:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When you bless food,\Nit jumps quite a few points in the calibrated energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.02,0:12:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You actually transform food.\NThat which is made by love
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.05,0:12:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates much higher than that\Nwhich is made by machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.05,0:12:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Very often makes you go weak, actually.\NThere's a couple brands of cat food
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.05,0:12:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,which I won't mention\Nthat my cat won't touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.05,0:13:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We calibrated them. They're below 200.\NAmazing. Cat knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.78,0:13:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't eat calibrated food below 190.\NThey're established brands.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.78,0:13:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I think of all those poor kitties out there\Nbeing forced to eat that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.04,0:13:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So we bless our kitties' food too.\NGod bless this food for our kitty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.04,0:13:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?\NBless your kitty's food.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.83,0:13:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I started to say that was\Nit was really interesting for this new book.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.83,0:13:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This new book I'm just finishing.\NOh, God bless us when it's out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.83,0:13:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to tell the truth about everything.\NYou know how popular that will make you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.98,0:13:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a famous quote.\NI forgot who it was. Montaigne or somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.98,0:13:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, after you tell the truth, leave town.\NLaughter
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.39,0:14:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's funny.\NThe Ganges River
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.79,0:14:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is disgusting.\NLaughter
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.43,0:14:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I was once floating in the\NHuangpu River in Formosa, China
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.43,0:14:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,or some other place.\NIt was full of feces,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.43,0:14:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,dead bodies.\NI was laying in my bunk on a minesweeper
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.78,0:14:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and I hear the thump, thump, thump.\NAs we get out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.78,0:14:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a dead body.\NHis head is bumping against the...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.78,0:14:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what...\NSo the Ganges River goes by
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.78,0:14:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,100 metropolitan areas that all\Ndump their sewage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.78,0:14:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The sewage of 100 metropolitan areas\Ndumps into the Ganges River.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.91,0:14:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus countless dead bodies,\Nfeces of all kinds of animals, humans, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.91,0:14:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Ganges River,\Nhelp me God, calibrates over 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.52,0:14:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ganges River.\NThe Ganges River.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.76,0:14:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have permission, oh Lord.\NCalibrates over 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.76,0:15:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,505, 510,\N515.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.11,0:15:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the power\Nof spiritual intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.28,0:15:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,For thousands of years, the Hindus\Nworshipfully
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.28,0:15:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,bathed for purification\Nin the Ganges.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.34,0:15:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Ganges is 510.\NThat's higher than your tap water at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.68,0:15:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do the animals again.\NThat's the power of prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.93,0:15:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of prayer.\NSo, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.76,0:15:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,by being worshipful in the world,\None comes to a feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.76,0:15:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of safety and peace.\NAnd through prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.28,0:15:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way you are to the world,\Nonce you've owned
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.28,0:15:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and recontextualized\Nwho you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.98,0:15:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the way you are to the world\Nis a prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.65,0:16:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You are a living prayer.\NYou don't have to get out your silly prayer card
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.65,0:16:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and go through the recitation.\NBe that which a prayer is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.61,0:16:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the universe\Nautomatically responds to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.90,0:16:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So worshipfully,\Nin all the feces and dead bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.96,0:16:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and garbage,\Nthe Ganges River calibrates at
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.32,0:16:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,five something.\NIsn't that incredible, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.40,0:16:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So then the hippopotamus, you get the\Nat 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.40,0:16:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to figure out how to work this thing in here.\NAt 200, then, you see
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.40,0:16:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a shift of consciousness.\NYou go from those who live
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.40,0:16:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,rapaciously through the death of others\Nby breaking the back of their neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.72,0:16:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,by ripping out\Ntheir jugular vein,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.32,0:16:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see those that\Nnow survive by eating grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.32,0:16:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It still needs energy\Nfrom out there, but it's in the form of grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.40,0:17:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And now it's benign.\NIt doesn't have to kill anything
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.40,0:17:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to kill life to eat.\NBut you see the core of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.40,0:17:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,then is rapacious.\NNow here it becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.66,0:17:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,benevolent. So you see\Nthe emergence of benevolence
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.66,0:17:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the animal kingdom calibrated\Nat level 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.92,0:17:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're safer with a zebra\Nor a gazelle or a giraffe
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.92,0:17:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,than 85% of the people\Non the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.92,0:17:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll steal you\Nblind. Deer,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.30,0:17:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,bison, domestic pig, elk,\Ndairy cow, sheep,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.30,0:17:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,range cattle.\NNow when I calibrated some of these things,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.49,0:17:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes I did them too quickly.\NA reader of one of the books
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.49,0:17:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,sent me a letter.\NSo when you calibrate something,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.42,0:17:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized I'd made a difference in the\Ncalibration of elephants.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.42,0:17:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because\Nwhen you're doing calibrated energies,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.42,0:17:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're in a hurry, you may do\None time you picture
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.42,0:18:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a herd of African wild elephants.\NAnd one of those
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.96,0:18:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,elephants could be a male who's in\NMusk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.96,0:18:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Another time I picture\NIndian elephants. Another time
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.06,0:18:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember I did picture an Indian elephant\Nwith a mahat
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.06,0:18:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or what do they call them on the back?\NMahat pushing up a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.06,0:18:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you've got certain\Ncircus elephants. So it makes a difference
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.16,0:18:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,which of those elephants you picture.\NAnd I didn't always picture the same one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.16,0:18:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,One time I pictured, I remember, African\Nelephants in the wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.16,0:18:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And another I pictured a guy with a\Nhauta on his back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.16,0:18:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Also we process things differently.\NWe process how a thing looks,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.16,0:18:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,how it sounds, how it feels.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.16,0:18:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,when it gets down to microscopic\Ncalibration, we don't do microscopic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.16,0:18:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What we're trying to convey is a\Ngenerality. But there may be
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.38,0:18:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,research problems in which\Na variation of a couple of degrees
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.38,0:18:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is significant. In that point\Nyou have to be consistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.38,0:19:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're going to calibrate a\Nthing and what you're picturing is how your mother
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.70,0:19:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,feels or how she\Nlooks or how she sounded,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.70,0:19:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it's going to be different.\NSo you'll have to use the same
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.80,0:19:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,way every time you do it.\NSo I didn't realize
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.80,0:19:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that and I'm glad he brought it to my attention.\NThere was the elephants and there was some other
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.80,0:19:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,one in which I calibrated\Ndifferently. Oh, monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.08,0:19:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,See the monkeys in the African wild\Nand the tree, it gives you a different
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.08,0:19:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,energy than monkeys in a zoo\Nand gives you a different picture
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.08,0:19:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,than monkeys\Nthat hang out in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.18,0:19:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,places in India. The different monkeys will give you\Ndifferent calibrations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.08,0:19:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people are just trying to get a generality.\NReally what we usually ask is
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.08,0:19:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a thing is either\Nintegrous or not. That's the main thing we want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.08,0:19:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm not\Ngoing to say that these are exact.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.08,0:19:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They're probably plus or minus.\NIn the book we just finished we've got at least
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.08,0:20:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a thousand calibrations.\NLet's just see how accurate that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.08,0:20:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,book is.\NThe calibrations in the book I'm just finishing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.27,0:20:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,are very\Nmore than 1%, 2%.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.27,0:20:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The calibrations\Nlast time we did it was 3% but I corrected
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.40,0:20:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,some of them.\NPlus or minus 3%.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.52,0:20:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Before it goes into print\Nwe'll recalibrate them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.52,0:20:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do want to admit that error.\NThat's the tenth step in AA.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.23,0:20:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're wrong you admit it.\NSomething world leaders have never
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.23,0:20:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered.\NI've heard some of the biggest names in America
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.96,0:20:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,get up there and lie through their teeth and I say\Nwhy don't they just admit that and say
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.96,0:20:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah, I mean so.\NAnd go on with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.96,0:20:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean it's unbelievable.\NSo you just say yeah I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.28,0:20:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So here\Nwe see then and also a race horse
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.28,0:20:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is more evolved than a regular farm horse.\NSo when these animals become
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.28,0:21:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,involved with humans their consciousness\Nadvances. So a kitty cat
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.28,0:21:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,feline nature is\N240 but a house
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.28,0:21:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,cat jumps to about 250.\NAnd the same with the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.28,0:21:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,dog. He becomes a family\Ndog. He jumps to at least 5 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.28,0:21:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the monkeys that I was\Ncalibrating one time were friendly
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.28,0:21:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,happy monkeys at 250.\NA gorilla is a very nice
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.51,0:21:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,person to be with. Chimpanzees are\Nand as we said before
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.51,0:21:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Alex the gray\Ntrained elephant gray
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.51,0:21:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is 401.\NAlex actually knows how to think and so does
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.51,0:21:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Coco. And here\Ncomes love yelping up through the heart
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.02,0:21:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,chakra bypassing\Nthe whole rest of the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.02,0:21:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,animal kingdom. And you got\Na kitty's purr is 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.08,0:21:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A dog's\Nsongbird's song 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.08,0:21:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And a dog's wagging tail is 500.\NIsn't that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.08,0:22:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,amazing? So\Nconsciousness then is the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.40,0:22:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,essence of life. Life\Nin order to survive has to be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.40,0:22:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,self serving. So there's\Nno point in feeling guilty about
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.58,0:22:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,ego because\Nit had to be self
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.90,0:22:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,centered in order for you to get here.\NHowever then it evolves
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.90,0:22:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,past that and\Nthe spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.03,0:22:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,energy begins to flow at\N200. The transformation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.22,0:22:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,begins at 200.\NLet's just do that for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.57,0:22:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Kundalini energy\Nwe have permission in front of this audience oh lord
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.57,0:22:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to flow at 200.\NIt does not flow
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.57,0:22:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200. And the etheric\Nbrain does not exist below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.60,0:22:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The etheric brain starts\Nat 200 and it's a consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.60,0:22:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of the flow of the kundalini energy.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.76,0:22:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,people below 200 don't have an etheric brain.\NWhat's the point of faulting
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.76,0:23:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,them for being non-integrous?\NBy what way would they be?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.95,0:23:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got no\Nmeans of knowing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.75,0:23:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood.\NSo now here is your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.26,0:23:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,ego. As you can see\Nhe's evolved from the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.86,0:23:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to be with your ego is to\Nrealize that without your ego you wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.86,0:23:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,even be here. So thank you.\NThe other way
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.61,0:23:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to disarm is to not get polarized\Nagainst the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.61,0:23:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,To just know that the ego\Nand every time
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.61,0:23:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody jumps ahead of us in traffic\Nwe hate him, don't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.61,0:23:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He should die, shouldn't he?\NOf course he should die.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.44,0:23:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he's bad.\NPeople who get in front of us in traffic
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.20,0:24:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and drive slow are bad people.\NAnd we hate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.03,0:24:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of denying your ego\Nwhich led to World War II
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.03,0:24:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you see what happened with denial?\NIt cost the lives of 10 million people.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.86,0:24:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,10 million people\Ndied due to a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.86,0:24:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the best way to\Nde-energize the ego is to tell the truth about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.86,0:24:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You're greedy, yes.\NYou want more, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.69,0:24:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to be right, yes.\NOf course he wants to be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.93,0:24:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to win, right.\NHe wants to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.44,0:24:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to win.\NHe always wants to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.99,0:24:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So he hasn't learned yet.\NIt's better to succeed
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.99,0:24:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,than to win.\NIn the end what counts as succeeding
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.40,0:25:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,winning doesn't mean anything.\NEvery winner sooner or later
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.40,0:25:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is a loser.\NEvery winner is polarized
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.04,0:25:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually a loser\Nbecause he's playing the win-lose game.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.45,0:25:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We know from quantum mechanics\Nyou play win-lose often enough
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.45,0:25:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,sooner or later\Nthe 26th decimal point
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.45,0:25:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to come up and kick you in the butt.\NSo you listen to me now, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.27,0:25:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NIt's better to succeed
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.04,0:25:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,than to win.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.72,0:25:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the way we dissolve the ego\Nis through love,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.72,0:25:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,through compassion.\NNot because we read it in a book,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.72,0:25:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,not because Krishna said it,\Nnot because Jesus said it,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.13,0:25:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but because we see it for what it is.\NWhat else could the little bear in us do
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.64,0:26:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,except do all the candidate things\Nit's supposed to do for survival?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.64,0:26:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks he's supposed to win.\NOkay, go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.92,0:26:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's number one.\NWhat was the next slide after the last one?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.92,0:26:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we'll skip that one anyway.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.04,0:26:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we'll skip that one.\NAlright, we'll just blank it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.48,0:26:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nwe said it's a way to be in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.66,0:26:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you are\Nto the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.98,0:26:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to focus on that.\NI want you to focus on content all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.98,0:26:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the context.\NLook at the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.33,0:26:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You can waste all the lifetimes you wasted\Nfooling around with content.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.33,0:26:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you get your content\Nin context and not content,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.45,0:26:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that recontextualizes that content\Nand the content is no longer a problem to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.45,0:26:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to recontextualize\Nthe ego to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.00,0:27:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing but a teddy bear within you\Nwho's doing his duty to try and win
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.00,0:27:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because he thinks that's what he's supposed to do.\NHe thought that for
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.00,0:27:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,hundreds of millions of years.\NGood ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.56,0:27:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You go ahead, win for me.\NAlright.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.28,0:27:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,People constantly send me questions\Nabout various spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.40,0:27:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people are,\Noh that's really good, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.65,0:27:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave that on.\NThey're always asking me to calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.03,0:27:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody or some\Nentity on the other side or something
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.19,0:27:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I really don't want to calibrate.\NI don't like to be quoted as
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.64,0:27:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,he said so and so.\NIf you know
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.98,0:27:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what integrity is about then\Nyou don't have to calibrate a teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.98,0:28:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say, what is a\Npure spiritual pathway?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.01,0:28:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all,\Nit doesn't glamorize itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.43,0:28:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't\Ndramatize itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.43,0:28:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't come on with theatrical presentations.\NIt's non-exclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.80,0:28:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to sign up.\NNobody pays a penalty
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.40,0:28:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,if they decide to leave.\NThere's no dues.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.55,0:28:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't adulate the leader.\NWhere was the leader? That's just his job.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.93,0:28:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Leading or teaching. Teaching is a function.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.48,0:28:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the person serves that function.\NTherefore you call them
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.60,0:28:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,respect because he's fulfilling the function.\NJust like I do the milkman who delivers the milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.60,0:28:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The street cleaner cleans the street.\NWe accord them the respect
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.69,0:28:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,due to the fact that they fulfill their function.\NWithout their function
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.01,0:29:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we wouldn't exist.\NWhen garbage delivery
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.01,0:29:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,removal stops on the streets of New York City\Nit's really a disaster. I lived there through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.01,0:29:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And you really learn to respect\Nthe garbage man.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.01,0:29:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So we respect people\Nfor what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.97,0:29:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So adulation of gurus\Nis a great trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.97,0:29:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The gurus that fall into it\Nthere's a whole group of them
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.97,0:29:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,on the other side of the planet\Neight or nine of them
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.97,0:29:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,all fell at the same time.\NAnd I only realized
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.66,0:29:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,what the reason was.\NI was having breakfast with somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.66,0:29:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,who was a friend of Gopi Krishna\Npainted Gopi Krishna
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.66,0:29:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,who wrote the famous book on Kundalini energy.\NAnd he said
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.72,0:29:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,when he first went to India\Nhe says
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.72,0:29:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the Indian people explained to him\Nwe're not scrupulous here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.84,0:30:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, scrupulosity\Nis not a requirement
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.84,0:30:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of success in that culture.\NJust saying whatever you think will get the sale
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.57,0:30:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or win is fine.\NThere's nothing wrong with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.57,0:30:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,See, we grew up in a judo-Christian culture\Nin which that's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.05,0:30:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There it's not wrong.\NIt's a organic culture
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.60,0:30:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and snake charmers\Nand everybody who can
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.60,0:30:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,boon-boggle you and get your pennies\Ndo so.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.60,0:30:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's nothing wrong with it.\NSo there's no point in demonizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.88,0:30:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So a true teacher then\Nteaches from
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.88,0:30:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is.\NThe teacher is teaching from
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.88,0:30:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,what the teacher has become.\NDoesn't teach by
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.68,0:30:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,authority of external\Nlevels.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.09,0:31:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't quote something\Nand then quote it to you as a teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.85,0:31:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There's known as\Nit stands on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.46,0:31:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrous spirituality and truth\Nstands on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.52,0:31:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have quotes from famous\Npeople.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.52,0:31:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What famous people think about it\Nis totally irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.75,0:31:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It stands on its own.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.57,0:31:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has nothing to gain.\NNothing to be gained, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.18,0:31:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What it's looking for\Nis not looking for any kind of gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.18,0:31:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't need followers.\NWhy would they want followers?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.21,0:31:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine everywhere you go\Nthey're trailing behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.44,0:31:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You go to get on a streetcar\Nyou wonder if all your followers got in.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.76,0:31:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Everywhere you look you got followers.\NPower over others and controlling others.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.52,0:31:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A good teacher doesn't tell anybody\Nhow they should live.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.52,0:32:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Their personal life.\NWhat you should wear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.52,0:32:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What you should eat.\NWhy would a spiritual teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.52,0:32:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,be interested in your personal life?\NThat could be more and more boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.52,0:32:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Want to get divorced?\NIt's up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.62,0:32:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Want to stay with her? Fine.\NWant to eat meat? Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.62,0:32:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Want to eat meat on Fridays? Yep.\NEat meat on Fridays? Boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.20,0:32:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's worse than any other day, you know.\NEat meat on a good Friday, man,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.44,0:32:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and you are really...\NOr you gotta wear a hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.78,0:32:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you gotta wear a hat or not wear a hat.\NTake your hat off. Respect God.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.78,0:32:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Respect God.\NI don't know, put my hat on or off.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.44,0:32:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NAlright.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.01,0:32:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't need fancy strange garb.\NYou don't need long hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.68,0:33:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need sandals.\NYou don't need piety.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.42,0:33:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Piety is a strange thing.\NIt's a naturalness
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.32,0:33:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to the way you are within the world.\NTrue piety is worshipful
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.32,0:33:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in that\Nyou present
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.88,0:33:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you are\Nto divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.68,0:33:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,as what you have become.\NIn so doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.95,0:33:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,one serves God and one's fellow man.\NSo there's nothing to gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.42,0:33:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no desire to control people.\NHave them sign up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.42,0:33:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reward.\NYou sign up three of them
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.61,0:33:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and you get an extra $50.\NSo there isn't any market level marketing,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.68,0:33:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,multi-level marketing.\NThe thing stands on its own
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.25,0:33:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,due to its own integrity, you see.\NIt's not interested in money.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.17,0:34:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's interested in covering expenses.\NExpenses are quite high, by the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.52,0:34:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The Radisson cost you about 10 grand up in front\Njust to walk in the front door.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.16,0:34:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And there were other places we wanted to meet\Nand there was even more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.16,0:34:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So you cover the expense\Nand then you've got to have enough left over
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.16,0:34:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,for operations\Nbecause you have to have quite a sizable staff
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.16,0:34:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,as time goes on.\NYou've got half a dozen people
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.16,0:34:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,answering the phone and shipping out things\Nand mailing and answering questions
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.36,0:34:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and making reservations.\NSo instead from 12 to 2,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.36,0:34:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we'll stop at 12.30.\NAt 1.15 I'll meet with that group in the side room.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.42,0:34:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remembered somebody said\Nthere's leaflets telling you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.42,0:34:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,there's restaurants that'll give you a discount\Nif you go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.55,0:34:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And those leaflets are out there.\NSo we were talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.83,0:34:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need to calibrate a teacher\Nif you're comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.05,0:34:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because whether a teacher\Nis right for a prisoner or not depends.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.05,0:35:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,When you begin,\NI'll tell you a great place to begin
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.08,0:35:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's to join the scouts.\NBoy Scouts and Girl Scouts of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.08,0:35:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They calibrate way up there.\NThey calibrate way up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.18,0:35:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And Eagle Scout calibrates even higher.\NI forget what they calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.18,0:35:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's quite impressive.\NA good place to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.34,0:35:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Scouts start you off right at 4.50 or 4.60\Nor something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.34,0:35:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a hell of a good place to start.\NThat beats about 90% of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.34,0:35:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to start out at 4.60.\NSo you don't have to go
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.81,0:35:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to strange places and seek out\Npeople in esoteric garb.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.81,0:35:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Because those are dramatizations.\NAnd India is the home of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.91,0:35:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They've learned the art of spiritual seduction.\NThe art of spiritual seduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.91,0:35:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you're looking for\Nin a teacher is somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.05,0:35:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,who has the recognition\Nof the relatively erudite spiritual seekers
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.31,0:35:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,alias that you won't waste time.\NNot interested in status.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.01,0:36:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Not interested in control.\NNot interested in money.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.01,0:36:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't self-assert.\NDoesn't design any special titles.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.08,0:36:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the title of the teacher?\NWell, if you're teaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.52,0:36:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,then I guess teacher.\NIf you're a swimmer, you'd be swimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.52,0:36:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're a skier, you'd be the skier.\NThe group skier, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.52,0:36:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So teacher just does teaching\Nbecause that's the function.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.52,0:36:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So one is one's function\Nand one's function comes out
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.52,0:36:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of one's realization.\NSo the true teacher then
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.60,0:36:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is merely\Nthe reflection of the inner knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.99,0:36:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no personal self\Nthat decides to say this.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.08,0:36:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't process things.\NThere's no processing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.08,0:36:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It is that\Nand then speaks spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.08,0:36:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which it is.\NTherefore, there is no design.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.32,0:37:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything happens spontaneously.\NWhen you become
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.36,0:37:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you can be\Nto the utmost, to the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.36,0:37:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you are a prayer.\NRecitations are nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.78,0:37:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking about piety.\NThere's a certain level of which
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.72,0:37:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,piety is\Nnatural for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.79,0:37:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute I look at this audience,\NI feel worshipful.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.79,0:37:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And\Nif I don't watch it, tears begin to flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.88,0:37:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of joyful ecstasy.\NThen there's
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.78,0:37:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,another kind of piety\Nthat's sort of holier than now
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.78,0:37:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,piety.\NDraped in
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.78,0:37:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,robes and incense\Nand dingle bells and things.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.87,0:37:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of a dramatization.\NIt can itself become an addiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.87,0:38:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like asceticism.\NI went through asceticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.22,0:38:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You can live without anything.\NIt's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.22,0:38:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,However,\Nextreme poverty and asceticism
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.48,0:38:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes in itself an addiction.\NSo you transcend that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.51,0:38:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's alright to have stuff.\NYou don't have to have an aversion
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.50,0:38:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't have to have an attraction.\NSo what the person is looking for
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.59,0:38:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,when they want to calibrate a true teacher\Nis somebody who is naturally
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.59,0:38:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the expression of that which they have become.\NTherefore, they don't require
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.59,0:38:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,falsity\Nbecause all they are is just being
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.59,0:38:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that which they are.\NTo just be that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.29,0:38:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,To just be that which you are.\NLike Satchmo.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.36,0:38:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Just is who he is.\NLouis Armstrong calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.36,0:38:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,way up there, 5 or 10 or something.\NHe's one of the top guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.36,0:38:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Satchmo.\NJust came from universal love.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.36,0:39:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Just was what he was.\NDidn't have to make any poses.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.42,0:39:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't have to control people.\NDoesn't need anything from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.64,0:39:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't want to tell you\Nwhat you should wear,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.64,0:39:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,who you should be with,\Nall about your sex life,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.86,0:39:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,what you should eat,\Nmeat, fish, what.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.86,0:39:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-controlling.\NSo freedom then.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.76,0:39:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom is the natural expression\Nand then
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.88,0:39:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you find a teacher that you're comfortable with.\NAnd as you grow along
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.88,0:39:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you may go through\Na progression of teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.84,0:39:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the teacher who is right\Nsolves this problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.84,0:39:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you're ready to move on to another teacher\Nbecause you've moved along.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.84,0:39:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've learned what this teacher has to teach.\NThe actual teaching of course
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.04,0:40:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that goes on\Nfrom an advanced consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.04,0:40:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is not the content at all.\NIt's the frequency and the vibration
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.04,0:40:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of the field.\NIt's the frequency and the vibration
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.04,0:40:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of the aura, of the field\Nof the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.55,0:40:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,See, content is in here.\NThis is prayers and mantras and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.55,0:40:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And what makes them work\Nis because it generates a field.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.64,0:40:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But what's actually teaching\Nis the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.74,0:40:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the field.\NThe frequency of the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.00,0:40:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of the vibration of the aura\Nof the teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.35,0:40:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,by your ascent becomes\Ntrained in your own aura
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.35,0:40:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time.\NThat's what the Buddha meant
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.35,0:40:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,when he said.\NThe teaching
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.99,0:40:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in my understanding\Nmy inner understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.99,0:40:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is the frequency and the energy\Nof that has within it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.99,0:41:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the information.\NThe information that you need to know
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.31,0:41:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,at a certain point is encoded in the frequency.\NHaving brought that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.14,0:41:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,frequency into your own aura\Nyou're going to reach
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.43,0:41:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a state eventually\Nthose of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.62,0:41:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How many here are going to be enlightened?\NEverybody! God bless you!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.78,0:41:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Why else would you be here?\NThat's what I prepare
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.74,0:41:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,people for along the whole trip.\NBecause in either this
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.12,0:41:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,or some lifetime\Nyou reach the final door
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.19,0:41:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and at that point\Nyou're not going to remember
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.67,0:41:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,anything because you don't have\Nany memory to remember it with.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.67,0:41:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, oh I'll remember that\Nwhen I get there. No you won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.89,0:41:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There ain't nothing to remember.\NThey took away your cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.15,0:41:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You forgot God's\Nnumber. What the hell was his number?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.78,0:42:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No, because it's very\Nvivid, the knowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.64,0:42:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowingness replaces\Nthinkingness. You don't need thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.64,0:42:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what you need is knowingness.\NSo as you walk through the last
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.22,0:42:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,door, there's a moment of\Nterror because
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.44,0:42:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing left to surrender\Nto God except
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.44,0:42:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the self.\NThat which you think you have been
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.54,0:42:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,through all eternity.\NThe core of life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.54,0:42:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You now surrender to God\Nand now
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.53,0:42:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you die for the first\Nand only and last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.82,0:42:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The other time you just left the body.\NThat's why I don't go for melodrama
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.82,0:42:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,about dying. Give me a break.\NHow many times have we all died here?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.43,0:42:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Quizzle. You're out of the body.\NI mean what's the big deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.43,0:43:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All the drama on this side. God bless it.\NNow this time
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.87,0:43:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you're really going to need\Nthe knowingness because without the knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.87,0:43:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it's terrifying to walk\Nthrough because you realize you are
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.83,0:43:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,actually walking into actual\Ndeath. This is death
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.83,0:43:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that you do have to give up your\Nlife. Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.11,0:43:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the full understanding of that\Ncomes forth. Then
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.56,0:43:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,out of non-thinkingness because\Nyou're beyond thought at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.56,0:43:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no thinking to think with.\NThere's no thinker left.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.94,0:43:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Comes the knowingness.\NSo the teacher must have
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.26,0:43:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute concrete certainty.\NThe only concrete
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.77,0:43:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute certainty for which\None is taking karmic responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.77,0:43:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,for that which is being said\Nbecause everything I say I take
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.77,0:43:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic responsibility and I'm very\Naware of the price of error.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.77,0:43:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,At the doorway the knowingness\Ncomes to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.08,0:44:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,To surrender life itself.\NThe knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.15,0:44:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Comes out of like Zen.\NTo walk straight ahead no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.56,0:44:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all fear is\Nillusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.52,0:44:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe except this instance.\NThat's okay for 99.99%.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.18,0:44:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about the last iota?\NAnd there takes the great
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.04,0:44:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,courage. There you walk\Nthrough it and you experience
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.20,0:44:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,death. I won't kid you.\NAgonizing. You experience
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.20,0:44:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of death itself.\NSo what carries you through
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.41,0:44:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is the energy field of the\Naura. See the frequency
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.41,0:44:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,cast within it the information.\NNothing said that to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.51,0:44:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no other beings there.\NForget other beings. There are no other
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.51,0:44:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,higher beings.\NNo spiritual guides or whatever crap
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.51,0:44:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,they think about. No such thing.\NI've never met any along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.51,0:45:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And they aren't there either.\NThere is the inner knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.51,0:45:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to walk straight ahead no matter what\Nall fear is illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.51,0:45:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore I repeat\Nwhere I heard it originally apparently
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.51,0:45:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,from the aura of the Buddha or\None of the great
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.40,0:45:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,teachers of the ancient Vedas. I don't know\Nwhere in history. I never tracked it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.40,0:45:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was there.\NIt's encoded as a
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.88,0:45:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,frequency. And when\Nyou need it you've reached that frequency
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.94,0:45:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and at that frequency the knowingness\Nis known.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.74,0:45:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And you walk through.\NAnd then all splendor
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.09,0:45:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,shines forth.\NSo that's the purpose then
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.40,0:45:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is\Nto share with
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.47,0:46:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the students\Nwhere the teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.63,0:46:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,has been and where\Nhe knows he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.66,0:46:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And doesn't pretend to be beyond that.\NThe integrity of many organizations
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.01,0:46:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,like AA etc.\NYou see all of them humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.01,0:46:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Humility is what?\NIt's the courage to tell the truth about yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.17,0:46:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And the true teacher will say\Nyou know I got this far
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.17,0:46:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you want to go farther\Nyou'll have to find somebody who teaches that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.17,0:46:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Teachers of religion\Ndo not teach enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.49,0:46:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll say look\NI belong to a religion and we teach
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.49,0:46:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,such and such and that's as far as we go.\NSo that person is being honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.49,0:46:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He says I only believe in God transcendent.\NThe world of the mystic
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.88,0:46:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is still\Nsuspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.60,0:46:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We gave up burning them at the stake.\NOr putting them under house arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.60,0:46:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But\NGalileo was put under house arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.85,0:47:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.\NSo you move from religion
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.20,0:47:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which has its core spirituality\Nand you say I want to transcend religion
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.20,0:47:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go\Nto where religion came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.20,0:47:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to rediscover\Nthe spiritual core out of which
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.20,0:47:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a religion arose.\NThen you have to go from
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.80,0:47:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,traditional religion into spirituality.\NAnd of course that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.80,0:47:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,brings you in contact with the world's great religions.\NThe great
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.89,0:47:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Vedas out of India.\NThe enlightened masters
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.89,0:47:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,arose in the Vedic\Nand Aryan culture
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.89,0:47:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of ancient India.\NThey were enlightened gurus
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.89,0:47:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,by 7,000 BC.\N7,000 BC.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.48,0:47:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They were a great\Nenlightened master.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.74,0:47:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,5,000 BC.\NThe Buddha came along
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.00,0:48:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,500 BC\Nand the reason the Buddha was never a Christian
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.25,0:48:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is Christ hadn't been born for another 500 years.\NHere people
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.00,0:48:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,knock the Buddha. He's not a Christian.\NHe's a heathen.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.41,0:48:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ wasn't born yet.\NSo the core of all truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.04,0:48:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So the teacher has to\Nhave humility
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.45,0:48:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of knowing where the limitations are.\NWillingness to admit a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.87,0:48:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If I miscalibrated monkeys\NI miscalibrated monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.93,0:48:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I must have been monkeying around\Nthat day.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.05,0:48:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Monkeying with the figures.\NAlright.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.53,0:48:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just wanted to make that clear.\NThat by their fruits
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.92,0:48:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you should know them.\NDon't be impressed by the miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.40,0:49:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The miraculous is nothing at all.\NOnce the kundalini energy comes up
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.43,0:49:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it performs the miraculous.\NThere's no
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.65,0:49:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you that performs the miraculous.\NThere are no
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.65,0:49:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,miracle workers.\NAnd the kundalini is very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.75,0:49:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It will heal that\Nto which it is destined to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.75,0:49:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't select it.\NYou don't think oh look at that poor sick woman there.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.94,0:49:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She's all crippled up.\NAnd start sending her healing energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.94,0:49:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a break. No.\NThe kundalini energy does it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.55,0:49:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't consult you at all.\NIt just goes there.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.61,0:49:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of a sudden the lady who's all\Ntwisted up looks at you and goes
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.61,0:49:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,walks away.\NThere isn't any you
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.00,0:49:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that did that.\NAlso the kundalini energy is not
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.16,0:49:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,predictable.\NYou can't perform miracles on the hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.57,0:50:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NBecause it acts of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.73,0:50:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a divine energy.\NIt's like it comes from on high.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.73,0:50:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a conduit.\NYou're like a telephone, telegraph
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.73,0:50:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,radio station.\NAnd it goes there.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.73,0:50:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just a radio station.\NYou're not the source of that divine energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.44,0:50:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've all become\Nspiritually perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.78,0:50:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Your past is healed.\NYour future is certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.83,0:50:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And from this point on\Nwe have become
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.98,0:50:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we are each one of us\Na prayer to this world
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.98,0:50:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and a blessing.\NAt 1.15 I'll meet with the Wisconsin group.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.63,0:51:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll slice cheese and sausage.\NAt 1.30
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.04,0:51:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the main group will resume.\NSheboygan is the world's foremost
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.04,0:51:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,producer of sausage.\NBoy, I'll tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.74,0:51:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,good old Wisconsin summer sausage.\NWell, we met with
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.35,0:51:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a group there.\NSo we're a little bit late.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.89,0:51:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't know how long it would take\Nto get in town, out of town
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.89,0:51:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and meet with the group and get here.\NI wanted to just bring
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.37,0:51:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the group did bring up\None of the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.20,0:51:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual errors is\Nthere's two of them. One is falling into the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.20,0:51:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The upper astral, the middle astral.\NWhich the New Agers tend to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.27,0:51:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Middle astral more.\NAnd then altered states of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.27,0:51:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,See, altered states of consciousness\Nlike learning biofeedback
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.27,0:52:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to go into alpha states, etc.\NAnd various altered breathing styles.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.27,0:52:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything that's artificial.\NYou can create an altered state
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.27,0:52:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,which is interesting.\NYou can do astral projection
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.27,0:52:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and all kinds of wondrous tricks with it.\NBut it is not the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.38,0:52:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, you don't have to do anything\Nto make a thing happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.38,0:52:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's dualistic.\NThere's a you doing a certain practice
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.38,0:52:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to make a thing happen.\NYou understand? That's dualistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.96,0:52:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In reality, nothing is causing anything.\NSo to save 60 lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.47,0:52:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I guarantee 60 lifetimes\Nif you get
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.94,0:52:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that the way to be in the world\Nyou see
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.71,0:52:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is like allowing.\NNothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.32,0:53:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the big bypass.\NToday I want you to forget cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.32,0:53:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing anything.\NThere is no cause
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.42,0:53:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in this world\Nanywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.42,0:53:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is spontaneously\Nbeing what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.41,0:53:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the\Ninfinite field of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.64,0:53:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality\Nbecomes actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.64,0:53:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the cloud\Ncoalesces out of the totality
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.15,0:53:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of the sky\Nand its potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.21,0:53:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is expressed then\Nwithin form.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.21,0:53:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But nothing is causing the cloud\Nto be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.21,0:53:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you got that last slide?\NThe potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.02,0:53:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes the actuality.\NThe potentiality is the product
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.02,0:53:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of evolution.\NPotentiality is in the non-linear domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.02,0:54:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really within\Nthe morphogenetic fields
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.80,0:54:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of, what's his name?\NSo the potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.98,0:54:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in form. So evolution occurs\Non the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.98,0:54:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in the invisible realm\Nand then by intentionality
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.08,0:54:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it manifests forth.\NSo you see there's no transitory
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.08,0:54:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,forms. You don't\Nsee a zebra
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.08,0:54:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming a horse.\NIt comes out zebra, it comes out
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.08,0:54:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,horse, it's complete and total when it comes off.\NSo the evolution is
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.08,0:54:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,occurring in the invisible domain\Nand then it appears
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.08,0:54:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,so that evolution and creation are one\Nand the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.08,0:54:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution is the way creation appears\Nsequentially to perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.08,0:54:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Continuous and ongoing.\NThat which has no beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.65,0:54:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and no end.\NNo, the previous one.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.10,0:54:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Content, field and\Ncontent and field.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.09,0:55:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that wonderful thing.\NYeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.97,0:55:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to get God on the slide here.\NThis is content. This is Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.73,0:55:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,science, you see.\NNow whether a thing manifests or not
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.12,0:55:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on several\Nthings. One is
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.12,0:55:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the favorability of conditions.\NTherefore you can put
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.31,0:55:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,a seed in the ground.\NNow what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.69,0:55:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is it has a\Npotentiality to become an
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.79,0:55:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,actuality. But nothing\Ncan force it to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.85,0:55:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Under favorable conditions\Nthen. So it's
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.01,0:55:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic design is that under favorable\Nconditions, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.01,0:55:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality becomes an actuality.\NBut you cannot
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.43,0:55:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,force a flower to do anything.\NYou can't force it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.78,0:56:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to become a turtle either.\NPeople don't believe in karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.20,0:56:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, well how come a butterfly isn't a turtle then?\NTell me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.20,0:56:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because\Nthe flower has the karmic propensity
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.20,0:56:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to become a flower and nothing else.\NSo truth cannot be
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.35,0:56:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,defined except within context.\NExcept within context
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.35,0:56:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing is true except under certain\Nconditions. So the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.35,0:56:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions are the proximate field.\NThis is the weather,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.54,0:56:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,this is political climate,\Nmany other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.54,0:56:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Cause is not the\Nexplanation of phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.59,0:56:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how do you explain phenomena?\NFirst of all, phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.81,0:56:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is an arbitrary selection.\NEverything is in continuous flow
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.81,0:56:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you say\Nthis moment started now, this moment
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.81,0:56:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,started there, well you just picked it out of there.\NThere is no such thing as a moment there.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.81,0:57:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,A moment is all in your mind.\NThere are no moments in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.42,0:57:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore there is no happenings to explain.\NIsn't that nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.52,0:57:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Gets you off the hook with everything.\NSo one
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.30,0:57:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,inherits by karmic\Nevolution over
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.43,0:57:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,great periods of time\Na potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.26,0:57:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which by intention\Nor by the power of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.26,0:57:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes an actuality.\NI always liken
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.82,0:57:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,God as an infinite\Nelectromagnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.27,0:57:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you know how an electromagnetic\Ncondenser works.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.27,0:57:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,An electromagnetic condenser is still\Nuntil you present it with a charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.27,0:57:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And then\Nthe charges line up on the
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.27,0:57:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,electromagnetic condenser\Nequal and opposite
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.07,0:57:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to the charge.\NIf you present it with a lot of electrons
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.07,0:58:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it will automatically, so it\Nonly reacts to that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.07,0:58:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,presented to it.\NThe field of consciousness then
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.09,0:58:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is still unmoving,\Ndoesn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.09,0:58:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is\Nthe giant electromagnetic field
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.70,0:58:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in which all the us\Nlittle iron filings line up
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.70,0:58:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of our design.\NSo freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.04,0:58:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is the freedom to choose\Nwithin the options
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.04,0:58:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have karmically earned\Nto have presented to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.36,0:58:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot say yes or no\Nto becoming a turtle.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.36,0:58:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nthat which you have become
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.20,0:58:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,gravitates by\Nthe power of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.25,0:58:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you have become\Nautomatically aligns itself
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.25,0:58:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in the field over here.\NBecause that which you
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.41,0:59:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore, there is nobody\Npaddling your canoe except you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.41,0:59:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody has the rudder on your\Ndestiny except yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.60,0:59:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is a little scary.\NThat which by choice
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.45,0:59:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you choose determines\Nwhere you settle out
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.45,0:59:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,within the field.\NSo like is attracted to like
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.45,0:59:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Neach one filters.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.55,0:59:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So as we leave the body one automatically\Nis aligned
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.55,0:59:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with the field of that which\Nyou have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.19,0:59:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no necessity for an arbitrary god\Nto give you a good smack
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.21,0:59:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,for being bad.\NBecause you are in hell already.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.53,0:59:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Having chosen hell\Nsome guy will blow up a big building
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.79,0:59:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and do that.\NHe says, well I know I am destined for hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.01,0:59:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He was probably correct.\NHaving been there I don't advise it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.56,1:00:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Blowing up people\NI guess that's just the upper level of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.77,1:00:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing\Nanything out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.04,1:00:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore\Nthere is no such thing
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.27,1:00:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,as a perpetrator or a victim.\NEach one brings to himself
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.29,1:00:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,his own\Nconsequences of his own karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.32,1:00:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Each person\Nat birth
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.80,1:00:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,already has a calibrated level of consciousness.\NEach person at birth
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.80,1:00:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is born in the optimal\Nkarmic possibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.09,1:00:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The circumstances\Nof your birth are perfect
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.09,1:00:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,for that which you are\Ndesigned for learning.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.37,1:00:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask that\Nwith this group.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.50,1:00:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The circumstances of one's birth\Nare perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.72,1:01:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The circumstances of your birth\Nare perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.72,1:01:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,For that which you have become\Nup to this point.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.90,1:01:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Cold Wisconsin winters\Nwas perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.42,1:01:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,18 miles a day on a bicycle\Nin a Wisconsin winter
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.42,1:01:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with 100 pounds of newspapers\Nwas what I needed
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.68,1:01:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to learn\Nwhat would you call it?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.03,1:01:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Steely determination no matter what.\NDespite anything
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.22,1:01:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you grit your teeth and you do it.\NHow to walk ahead straight ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.60,1:01:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That got me through medical school.\NYou try working your way through medical school
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.60,1:01:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean.\N100 hours a week as an intern for $100 a month.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.60,1:01:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,People talk about low paying nowadays\Nit makes me laugh.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.28,1:01:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,$100 a month for 100 hours a week.\NSo the steely
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.30,1:01:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,determination that it takes\Nso I guess that was
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.30,1:02:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,perfect to learn that\Nsteeliness.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.30,1:02:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That walk ahead no matter what.\NAnd then when the great test
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.30,1:02:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of it came\Nthe walk straight ahead
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.39,1:02:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what\Ncame up in spades.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.39,1:02:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well I didn't realize that.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.92,1:02:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no point bewailing one's birth\Nthere's no point feeling sorry
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.92,1:02:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for people.\NSentimentality calibrates below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.92,1:02:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Gets a lot of air time.\NEverybody's always
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.79,1:02:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for the culprit.\NIt's always somebody's fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.62,1:02:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So the newest paradigm of reality\Nis nothing is anybody's fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.62,1:02:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always the fault of somebody out there.\NSociety, society.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.62,1:02:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody is\Nthe perpetrator victim
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.13,1:02:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the core of Marxism\Nand calibrates 130.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.36,1:03:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The perpetrator victim model\Nhas had a very derogatory
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.36,1:03:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,detrimental\Neffect on the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.06,1:03:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,quality of the fabric of society\Nin which one is always looking for
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.06,1:03:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the guilty\Nthe guilty one.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.83,1:03:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NOh truth keeps
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.45,1:03:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,disappearing all the time.\NWhat did we pay rent on?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.28,1:03:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She's saving electricity\NI know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.86,1:03:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the infinite\Ninfinite
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.76,1:03:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,all encompassing fuel\Nof consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.76,1:03:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,omnipotent, omnipresent,\Nomniscient.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.64,1:03:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,As one lets go of the limitations\Nof form
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.96,1:03:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and one progresses beyond this\None comes into the field
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.96,1:03:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of knowingness.\NThat's what speaking
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.38,1:04:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,what is speaking to you today\Nis knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.26,1:04:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I have nothing to do with it.\NIt speaks spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.38,1:04:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening of its own\Nwhich is a fact
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.88,1:04:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes to you\Nwith sudden surprise.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.68,1:04:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the belief there's a you\Ncausing all these things to happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.68,1:04:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you the trick of the ego\Nis to claim credit for a thing
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.81,1:04:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I caught it once doing it.\NThe ego claims credit
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.32,1:04:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,for what is actually spontaneous\Nand it takes about
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.32,1:04:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,1 ten-thousandth of a second\N1 ten-thousandth of a second
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.74,1:04:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that's when the Buddha\Nsaid you could glimpse
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.72,1:04:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the ultimate infinite truth\Nis between two thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.72,1:04:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,no it's not between two thoughts\Nit's right prior to two thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.11,1:05:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,between two thoughts\Nsort of sets up the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.20,1:05:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Newtonian image\Nof thoughts being like
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.20,1:05:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,billiard balls\Nwhere one thought is causing another one.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.20,1:05:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Every thought is arising\Nout of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.68,1:05:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Every thought is arising\Nout of nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.32,1:05:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Prior to that thought\Nthere is nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.16,1:05:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll find right now\Nat the back of your mind
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.54,1:05:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a still field\Nwhich doesn't do anything
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.92,1:05:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or say anything\Nbut registers everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.92,1:05:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unverbal.\NThe capacity for hearingness
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.11,1:05:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity for knowingness\Nthe mind is actually silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.62,1:05:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the silence\Narises
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.63,1:05:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,out of sort of an\Nof a thought
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.63,1:06:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,dogginess\Nand then if you allow that
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.75,1:06:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,thought to progress\Nit's going to become old rover
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.75,1:06:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's going to be old rover\Nwas hit by the truck
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.75,1:06:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then how we all cried\Nredoing rover
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.00,1:06:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,getting run over by the truck\Nrerunning the whole story
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.12,1:06:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in your head.\NNo, you see that coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.99,1:06:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not even rover yet.\NBy focused meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.99,1:06:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see how this\Nonce you let it loose
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.99,1:06:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it begins to amplify itself\Nbecause we're enamored of our thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.11,1:06:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,As you watch the thoughts\Nyou see the thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.65,1:06:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,they crest and then they fall away.\NIn meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.65,1:06:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,be quiet\Nbecause contemplation
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.65,1:06:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is a way of being in the world\Na contemplative way of being in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.91,1:07:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore it's continuous\Nwhereas meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.97,1:07:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to be something\Nin which you separate yourself from the world
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.07,1:07:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,go off, go into a very special state\Nall kinds of postures
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.07,1:07:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and breathing and weird things\Nthat's separate from all dayness
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.48,1:07:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so you go into a great state\Nin meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.48,1:07:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then you get up\Nand that's meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.48,1:07:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that much.\NMeditation is good for
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.57,1:07:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,discerning how all this happens\Nand
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.96,1:07:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in a focused meditation\Nas you watch
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.06,1:07:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the thoughts arise\Nyou'll see
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.06,1:07:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,they are like the cresting of a wave\Nand no sooner do they crest
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.06,1:07:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,then they're falling away\Nso thoughts are like music
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.06,1:07:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,no sooner do you hear the tone of the music\Nthat tone is already fading away
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.88,1:08:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,anxiety\Nor always trying to control the future
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.88,1:08:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,anticipate the future\Nso they live in front of the wave
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.17,1:08:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they're always one up\Nand always anxious about the next moment
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.17,1:08:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to control the next moment\Npeople who live on the back of the wave
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.56,1:08:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,are clinging to the moment\Nthat's just left
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.48,1:08:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,they can't let that last tone of music go\Nthey're trying to make it last longer
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.48,1:08:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so they're constantly ruminating\Nabout the past
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.48,1:08:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so these people are frightened of the future\Nclinging to the past
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.96,1:08:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so you focus your attention\Nyour awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.96,1:08:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,on the exact presence\Nof that which is the crest
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.25,1:08:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,now the crest itself\Nis arising out of an intention
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.25,1:08:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,intentionality of thinkingness\Nthis intentionality
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.48,1:08:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is an enamour, a hypnotic state\Nyou let go
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.64,1:08:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the wanting to think\Nand you'll find that thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.64,1:09:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming from an intention\Nand you can finally actually find
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.70,1:09:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the source within the silent field itself\Nand let go of the intentionality
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.70,1:09:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of thinkingness itself\Nwhat good is that
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.46,1:09:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you discover\Nthat it has no life of its own
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.46,1:09:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it's coming out of something else\Na life lived as a prayer
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.29,1:09:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,one's life lived as a contemplative style\Nis to me
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.84,1:09:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the most rapid\Nand rewarding
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.84,1:09:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,means of spiritual evolution\Nto be aware at all times
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.11,1:09:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you are\Nto be what you are
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.81,1:09:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,like a mudra\Nyou know what a mudra is
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.81,1:09:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a hand position\Nto be so that your life itself
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.23,1:09:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is a presentation to God\Nas you are
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.26,1:09:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I am as I am\Nto thee oh Lord
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.51,1:10:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and to thee do I surrender\Nthat which I have become
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.87,1:10:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,other than that\Nwhat would you have to do
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.87,1:10:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,there is nothing further\Nto do
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.90,1:10:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,one lives one's life\Nlike a mudra
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.54,1:10:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so to pray\Nthen
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.44,1:10:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,one holds one's consciousness\Nthusly
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.44,1:10:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the Holy Spirit knows\Nwhat you mean by that
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.14,1:10:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I've lost my dog\NI asked for a miracle
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.88,1:10:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to find my doggie\Nevery time Kitty gets lost
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.68,1:10:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I just go like that\Nand Kitty gets found
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.03,1:10:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I make a big donation\Nto the church
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.33,1:11:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the kundalini energy\Ndoes it for you
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.40,1:11:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand\Nspiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.39,1:11:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is effortless\Nlike a cork floating
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.57,1:11:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in the ocean\Nto be
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.59,1:11:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you are\Nin supplication to divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.59,1:11:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,already\Nsummons forth
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.70,1:11:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite powers of the universe\Nin your behalf
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.50,1:11:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to do anything else\Nthat which you have become
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.70,1:11:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is like a cork\Nand you automatically rise
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.86,1:11:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,not because there is a me\Ndoing that
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.40,1:11:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but by virtue of that\Nwhich you have become
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.44,1:12:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,one floats higher and higher\Nin the water
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.56,1:12:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,effortlessly\Nto me spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.58,1:12:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is effortless\Nit's a decision
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.54,1:12:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an intention\Nthat intention then aligns you
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.34,1:12:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,with whatever you need to be aligned with\Na decent regret
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.54,1:12:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,takes care of the past\Ntrust, faith and surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.28,1:12:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,takes care of the future\Nand in the present moment
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.63,1:12:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have any problems\Nconsequently
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.20,1:12:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,what would the mind think about\Nwhat would you think about mind
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.86,1:12:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you would probably fight for existence\Nare you going to fight for existence
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.86,1:12:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that which has no reality\Nyou don't have to be killed
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.68,1:13:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to kill your mind\Nyou don't even exist
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.35,1:13:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got it beat before it starts\Nso one more or less
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.32,1:13:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,lets go\Nand becomes
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.55,1:13:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you seek\Nbecause that which you seek
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.84,1:13:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is not different\Nthan that which you discover
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.81,1:13:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so\Nspiritual work
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.88,1:13:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is merely being thus\Nit's like the ultimate
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.92,1:13:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,yin posture\Nthe ultimate yin posture
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.40,1:13:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to get to the ultimate yin posture\Nyou go through
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.49,1:13:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual night\Nthe ultimate yang posture
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.93,1:14:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and you kill people for Jesus\Nyou kill infidels
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.93,1:14:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you hate evil\Nevil
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.93,1:14:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but those are all\Nthe archetypes we go through
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.93,1:14:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,as we evolve spiritually\Nyou see
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.27,1:14:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to cross over 200\Nis merely an intention
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.27,1:14:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,as I say\Nif you're a boy scout or a bro scout
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.40,1:14:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,boy scouts are 450\Neagle scouts are 460
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.62,1:14:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,same for both the girls and the boys\Nthat's when hell of an integrity starts in life
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.91,1:14:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to live by integrity\Nhelpfulness
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.91,1:14:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,kindness, consideration, cordiality\NI mean those are
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.91,1:14:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you're halfway there already\Nas I say
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.91,1:14:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and when you get that master\Nmove on
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.76,1:15:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the minute you align to\Nintegrity
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.76,1:15:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in any of its forms\Nthe minute you begin to
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.76,1:15:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,really\Nappreciate beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.89,1:15:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it can start anywhere\Nyou can be walking through the woods
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.89,1:15:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly\Ntime stops
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.89,1:15:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,there's this absolute stillness\Nand you realize
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.02,1:15:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that something has just happened\Nand as everybody
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.02,1:15:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is arrived\Nthe Kundalini energy
