Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.40,1:17:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is primarily, I'm talking now in a right-handed person, is primarily left\Nbrain. It's concerned with survival. This and that. It has to stay alert to
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.25,1:18:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,survive. So the left brain then, sensory input goes very fast via the relay\Ncenter in the thalamus. The fast track
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.03,1:18:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is to the emotional center in the amygdala. You don't have to remember\Nthese names. I don't remember them myself. That's why they're printed up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.52,1:18:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You study all this, you pass the exam, you get a straight A, you forget it, like that.\NHow often do you run into an amygdala in your everyday life, you know? All right, so
