Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.42,1:18:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it's relayed to the emotional center. Now there's a slow track, a slow track, that\Ngoes to the prefrontal cortex and then to the amygdala. I've got a spotter
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.70,1:19:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere, yeah. So although the brain gets the message sooner or later, it's,\Nit's... So the fast track is this way to the emotional center. Kill. Prefrontal
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.78,1:19:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,cortex says,\Nsinful, but you've already decided to kill him. Now you attenuate it, but the killer came up first.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.92,1:19:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you're hit with the guilt of the killer, too. Not only did you think of killing him,\Nnow you feel, oh God, I'm sorry I thought that. Oh, you know, dear, dear, you know, I confess that I
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.15,1:19:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,thought of killing somebody. That experience, then, is stored in the hippocampus. The hippocampus\Nis where we store memory. So what kind of memories of the past does the person
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.89,1:19:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,who is not spiritual hold? Negative ones. Resentment, anger. He builds up a hit list\Nof all his enemies, because it's memory. When he goes into memory, it's all of painful hatred,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.34,1:20:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,guilt, envy, jealousy, competition, get even, revenge, because that's what he's\Nstoring.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.60,1:20:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He's stored up in his hippocampus. His experience of the world was that of an animal. So the\Nunattenuated ego, then, is the animal. There's nothing in your ego that you don't see in the
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.39,1:20:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,animal kingdom. Everybody's ego is on display every day in Monkey Island. Territorial dispute,\Nalpha males, who's going to get the alpha female, who gets more, bites, scratch, tear, hate.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.29,1:20:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When you look at what people die for,\Nthey'll show a thing from some place in North Africa, usually. As far as the eye can see,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.95,1:21:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing but dust and sand. Dust and sand. That's all there is. No water, no gold,\Nno nothing. And they kill each other by the thousands. So who's going to own this?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.61,1:21:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They're dying over this? When you see pictures of it, you say, you've got to be kidding.\NYou've got to be kidding. 500 miles of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.29,1:21:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,500 miles of nothing. They're going to kill each other over that. So the animal, then,\Nunattenuated. This is consciousness level below 200. People above 200 presume that other people
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.38,1:21:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,are like you. I'm going to tell you something that's going to save your life and that of\Neverybody on the planet. They do not think like you. They do not think like you at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.84,1:22:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They do not think like you. They do not think like you.\NThey'll take your eye teeth, folks. Not because they're bad, because they're good. Good animals
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.52,1:22:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,take everybody's eye teeth. It's their duty, you see. I once applied for a job. It was\Nin Wisconsin, too, I think. And you're supposed to sell peanut vending machines to retired
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.68,1:22:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,farmers. I think they're 25 bucks a piece. And the pitch was, you just go around and\Ncollect the money. We've got a new version of that on TV. ATM machines and various things.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.84,1:22:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And you put them in filling stations. So the guy pictures,\Nhe's going to drive around in his old pickup truck and dump out all this money.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.64,1:22:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What you don't tell him is that only happens once a year.\NIt's full of pennies, all right, but it takes a year.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.70,1:22:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So I got, you know, this is ripping off old people for their retirement money,\Nand it's completely fraudulent. And you know what he said to me, the training guy who was
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.48,1:23:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to sign me up as a salesman? He says, if you don't get their money, somebody else will.\NRemember that. If you think other people are like you, they're not. Because if they don't get
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.53,1:23:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,your money, somebody else will, is the prevailing message, okay? I don't want to make you paranoid,\Nexcept it's best to be paranoid. Now, paranoia is what we substitute before spiritual vision.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.65,1:23:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say when the third eye of the Buddha body opens up, you have discernment. But until that\Nhappens, you're anybody's company.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.38,1:23:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You're anybody's victim. All right, above 200, what happens? The consciousness now shifts. So\Nbelow 200, you got left brain dominance. You live in a linear domain. Everything is stressful,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.20,1:24:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,releases adrenaline. You get cellulase alarm reaction, resistance, and then finally exhaustion.\NYou get cannons, fight or flight reaction. You're constantly reducing. It's an adrenaline world.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.97,1:24:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This suppresses the stress response.\NIt suppresses the killer cells and depresses immunity. It suppresses the thymus. That's why
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.51,1:24:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. John Diamond recommended the thymus thump. Because this blows the acupuncture meridian.\NRepeatedly blowing the acupuncture meridian, because the various meridians are associated
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.44,1:24:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,with various organs in the body, you're constantly interrupting the energy to the heart,\Nor to the liver, or the stomach, small intestine, big intestine, whatever. You repeatedly do that,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.76,1:25:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and you finally kill yourself. Enough interference in the energy to the heart chakra, and the heart\Nbegins to get heart disease. Okay, so you keep blowing the acupuncture meridians, and you end up
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.56,1:25:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,with a negative physical state. Depleting is constantly shooting out adrenaline. You deplete\Nthe neurotransmitters in the brain. Which serotonin is the most effective? The serotonin is the most
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.36,1:25:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,common. You repair this with Prozac. A lot of people in our society suffer from a Prozac deficiency.\NAt least a third of the population at some time during their lifetime will be seriously depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.49,1:25:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is due to genetic factors. Genetic factors and depression and alcoholism tend to run genetically\Nin the same family. So if you've got a brother who's an alcoholic, the likelihood is about four
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.88,1:26:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,times higher that you may become depressed. So there's a genetic factor involved. There's a genetic factor\Ninvolved as well. Brain physiology and genetics. And what happens above consciousness level 200 now
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.79,1:26:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is in common parlance, you become a right brain person. We're talking about now is the right-handed\Nperson as the standard model. Left-handed person is the other way. Above consciousness level 200 now,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.08,1:26:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the kundalini energy begins to flow. And now the same sensor input goes fast track, fast track,\Nthrough the etheric brain to the emotional center. And your experience of the world is totally different.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.52,1:26:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Above 200, you think everybody in New York City is friendly. It's a fact. You can talk to any cab driver,\Nyou can talk to anybody. I'll do it on video. I'll just walk down the street, stop any stranger, and immediately start a conversation with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.65,1:27:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell do you think of so-and-so? Right where they're talking to you like they've known you for 20 years.\NIt's like we know each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.73,1:27:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean? The cab drivers are friendly. Everybody's friendly. Everybody's helpful. It's a wonderful place.\NWhy? Because you're experiencing a different world. This is a different world. So this person now in the emotional center says New York City is a wonderful place.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.82,1:27:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He stores in his hippocampus the memory of New York being friendly and helpful and happy.\NAll the waitresses were friendly. The cab drivers were great. The hotel was wonderful. What more can you ask?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.42,1:27:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NThey actually live in two different worlds. So when I say, don't think that these people do not think the way you do because they do not live in the same world you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.80,1:27:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You think everybody thinks in the same world. That's very naive. They do not live in the same world you do.\NYou say, how can people indulge in so much hate? Well, it's because they see a hateful world.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.40,1:28:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To you, that's astonishing. To them, they're surrounded by enemies. So forgiveness comes out of understanding.\NOh. They live in a world. They see that way. And that's why they think the way they do. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.68,1:28:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Their experience of the world is not the same. So to you, it seems crazy because you don't experience that kind of a world that would justify that kind of hatred.\NBlowing up busloads of children, bombing trade centers and God knows what all. Huh. Whatever they can think to blow up.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.00,1:28:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Conscious level about this.\NConsciousness level about 200, then the kundalini energy results in right brain dominance.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.74,1:28:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You now become dominated by the non-linear.\NAs I said, it's not what you say. You don't have to go through some kind of a ritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.60,1:29:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You become non-linear. You become the field.\NYou become the field. You begin to reflect the field and not the content of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.34,1:29:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you experience life as peace, you release endorphins instead of adrenaline.\NEndorphins are healing. They're anabolic.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.56,1:29:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Adrenaline is catabolic.\NEndorphins are anabolic and tend to heal.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.65,1:29:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So kundalini energy is a healing energy.\NIt supports the thymus and the killer cells which fight off infection.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.23,1:29:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It results in positive emotions.\NThe person is more peaceful, have greater immunity,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.69,1:29:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can say from personal experience,\Nhealing of the most incredibly impossible and curable conditions
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.45,1:29:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is the most important thing.\NIt happens of their own.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.98,1:29:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The acupuncture system remains imbalanced.\NIf it does go out of balance, it quickly is restored.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.04,1:29:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You get a positive kinesiologic response.\NAnd the track to the emotions is slower.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.70,1:30:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, the slow track is now to the emotions.\NThe fast track is to the cerebral cortex
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.36,1:30:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and specifically the etheric brain.\NSpecifically the etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.32,1:30:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So spiritual knowledge.\NThe understanding and learning is stored or is processed
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.40,1:30:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,through a special place in the prefrontal cortex of the etheric brain.\NWhat I just stated is true.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.32,1:30:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't read that any place, folks.\NYou heard it hurt here.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.59,1:30:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you, it took me a long time to draw this thing.\NI drew it about 18 ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.77,1:30:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I could not get it to be the way I knew it was.\NFinally it came out.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.43,1:30:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo what is the conclusion?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.19,1:30:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The importance is.\NIt's spiritual endeavor and intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.34,1:31:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Change the brain function, which changes how you experience the world,\Nchanges who you are, changes the body physiology,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.26,1:31:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,establishes an area for spiritual information in the right brain,\Ncerebral cortex and etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.14,1:31:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When I told you, you're not the same as those people, you are not.\NYou are not the same person.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.02,1:31:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You are.\NLet's go back to field and we got fuel and content.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.22,1:31:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That sort of pulls together a lot, doesn't it?\NHealing modality, physiology, spiritual work, kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.69,1:32:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It pulls it all together.\NSee here in left brain, you're identifying with just this and this believes in causality
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.10,1:32:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and duality.\NThis is where a Marxist lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.60,1:32:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He sees the world as perpetrator and victim, see.\NThen you begin to see that the worker and the capitalist are congruent.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.78,1:32:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The latest thing is to heap abuse on Walmart.\NWoe to those who heap abuse on Walmart.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.93,1:32:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, anything that becomes successful in our world, you know, becomes a target for\Nabuse, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.68,1:32:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Walmart is no exception.\NThis week's issue of Fortune magazine, good or evil, is Walmart good or evil, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.06,1:32:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's terrible.\NAnd of course, the thing about Walmart is that it's so big and successful and a certain
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.16,1:33:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,segment of society hates anything that's big and successful, no matter what it is.\NAnd of course, the question is who made Walmart rich and successful?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.67,1:33:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people here made Walmarts rich and successful?\NWe all made Walmart rich and successful.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.15,1:33:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Show me the evil capitalists when we're the ones that did it.\NWe went there because prices were cheaper.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.38,1:33:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What about mom and pop?\NWell, mom and pop get phased out, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.86,1:33:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When the telephone came along, the Pony Express died.\NSo you see evolution then goes through change.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.42,1:33:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean that there's a bad guy perpetrator and a poor victim.\NIt means that slavery passed as a human phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.44,1:34:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Slavery was widespread across the whole world for thousands of years.\NIn ancient Rome, the slaves outnumbered the free men ten to one.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.72,1:34:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the way life was.\NThen it slowly phased itself out in various parts of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.64,1:34:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a transitor.\NIt's a mandatory phase.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.64,1:34:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The same as women's position in society.\NIn an agrarian society, the woman's position was in the home and the guy was out in the
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.56,1:34:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,field.\NDid she want to go out there and sweat with the horses?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.30,1:34:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.\NI didn't want to go out there and sweat with the horses either.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.81,1:34:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In Wisconsin, they didn't have electric on the other side of the highway.\NNobody had a milking machine.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.61,1:34:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody could afford a tractor.\NYou had a big horse.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.05,1:34:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And a plow.\NAnd you were solid sweat from morning till night.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.94,1:35:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So he wasn't interested in washing the kids' clothes and bathing the kids and cooking and\Nall that crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.96,1:35:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,She took care of that.\NThe mother reigned supreme in the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.93,1:35:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Reigned supreme.\NModern society doesn't understand the position of the woman in the early part of the last
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.99,1:35:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,century.\NEspecially in the Midwest, everybody in Wisconsin knows what that means.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.96,1:35:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The mother, when a woman entered the room, you stood up.\NYou stood up.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.20,1:35:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And you honored her by opening the door for her.\NThe mother reigned supreme in the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.99,1:35:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And my grandmother would say, my grandfather would try to sneak through the living room\Nwith his pipe.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.27,1:35:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd try and hide it by his pants.\NAnd she'd run through and say, Frank, Frank, the drips.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.37,1:35:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You weren't allowed to use bad language in the presence of God.\NI knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.17,1:35:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.\NI knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.41,1:35:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.\NI knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.53,1:35:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.\NI knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.69,1:35:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.\NI knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.89,1:35:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.\NI knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.05,1:35:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.\NI knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.73,1:35:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Women had a separate entrance to the bar in the back.\NMen were vulgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.10,1:35:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They were at the bar.\NThey used bad language.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.88,1:36:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Women sat at the back.\NAnd men watched their language around women.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.65,1:36:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see how respected they were?\NThey were loved and respected.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.16,1:36:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The mother was supreme.\NOut in the field, the man ruled.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.28,1:36:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He ruled.\NBut he ruled over what?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.40,1:36:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The inanimate.\NIn fact, machines and crap like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.30,1:36:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Horses.\NShoveling horse poo.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.46,1:36:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,he was the king of shoveling cow poo\Ngetting sunburned and all sweaty
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.81,1:36:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course\NSaturday night you found out who was who
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.86,1:36:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Saturday night in Wisconsin\NI used to babysit all the time
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.38,1:36:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that's how I made a living\Nand I can still smell
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.16,1:36:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the smell of it\Nthe kerosene light, the kerosene lamp
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.01,1:36:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,every house you went to\Nsmelled like kerosene
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.95,1:36:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,then there was all those baby diapers hanging on\Nthe wood stove
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.63,1:37:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the big tub and the baby diapers\Nso the place smelled of kerosene
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.93,1:37:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and baby diapers\Nand sauerkraut
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.95,1:37:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but the woman, don't you see, was revered\Nshe wasn't being
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.70,1:37:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,abused\Nand kept out of the workplace
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.93,1:37:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,she didn't want any place in the workplace\Nshe didn't want any place in the workplace
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.65,1:37:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,she wasn't being abused\Nif I said to my grandmother
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.49,1:37:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,would you like to get a job\Nso she'd look at me like I was crazy
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.31,1:37:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,she had her job\Nand she was
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.47,1:37:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so the woman was really\Nin a way respected
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.99,1:37:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because she reflected an aspect of divinity\Nthat you don't get through the masculine
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.51,1:37:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,through the masculine\Nyou get the macho yang power
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.45,1:37:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was through the woman\Nthat you got nurturance
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.98,1:37:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it's nurturance by which we survive\Nyou know
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.37,1:38:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so I just wanted people to know how it really was\Nthen after World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.42,1:38:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the woman was needed in the workplace\Nand Rosie the Riveter
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.72,1:38:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we shifted around then because of Rosie the Riveter\Nbut again you see it's not victim
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.86,1:38:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to get past the whole victim perpetrator thing\Nit's not an evil society suppressing women
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.64,1:38:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,women weren't even interested in it\Nmy mother didn't hanker for a job at Woolworths
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.40,1:38:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter\Nthe world I brought up in
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.18,1:38:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,if a woman had to go to work\Nthe man was disgraced
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.98,1:38:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a disgrace\Nthat your wife had to go to work
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.68,1:38:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so\NI just want to show you how
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.80,1:38:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,twisting a paradigm\Nmakes a thing look like what it isn't
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.44,1:38:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you see\Nit isn't there's an evil perpetrator
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.70,1:38:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and an innocent victim\Nnobody had more power
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.34,1:39:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,than my mother in the house\Nmy father took his shoes off
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.57,1:39:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and you better not get mud on the rug\Nand people went
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.91,1:39:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to work\Nto bed when mother decided
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.68,1:39:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Nso power was equally distributed between the two
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.57,1:39:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody was perpetrating anybody\Nyou see retrospectively backwards in time
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.44,1:39:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you can project the perpetrator victim model\Nand what do you get out of that
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.92,1:39:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you get hatred\Nyou get hatred
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.77,1:39:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't get justice\Nyou get hatred
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.82,1:39:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,so what I meant to say\Nlaughter
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.49,1:39:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter\Nwhen you see men and women as equals
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.81,1:39:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize\Nall these positionalities are done
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.34,1:39:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,people get up there and they like to\Ngrandstand
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.34,1:39:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because their ego loves causes\Nthere's nothing the ego likes better than causes
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.34,1:39:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,save the grasshoppers\Nsave the forest
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.84,1:40:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,save women\NI'm always worried
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.34,1:40:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,where are they with the Iraqi women\Nthey're busy beating up
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.34,1:40:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the president about Iraq\Nwhere are the women now about the suppression of women?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.68,1:40:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in Iraq\NI haven't seen a parade yet
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.68,1:40:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't heard anybody on television\Nthese women can be killed
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.68,1:40:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,murdered at the guy\Nall he has to do is say
Dialogue: 0,1:40:14.68,1:40:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I divorce you\Nyou're done
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.68,1:40:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I suspect somebody told me\Nyou were flirting around
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.68,1:40:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,he can kill her\Nit's legal
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.91,1:40:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,where's the complaint about\Nyou call out a woman now
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.91,1:40:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,where it's real\Nwhere women are really being repressed
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.26,1:40:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,they weren't repressed in Wisconsin in 1930\Nlaughter
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.26,1:40:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so the field then\Neverything is the conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.26,1:40:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict\Nthe conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.42,1:40:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict\Nthe conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.42,1:40:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict\Nthe conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.83,1:40:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict\Nthe conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.52,1:40:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict\Nthe conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.52,1:40:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the consequence of the field\Nso everything is coming about
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.52,1:40:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is the consequence of the prevalence of a certain culture\Na certain culture
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.52,1:40:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,precipitates out\Njust like
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.71,1:40:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,so if you get beyond cause and effect\Nlet's go on to some more exciting slides
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.71,1:41:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,if you get beyond\Noh yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.03,1:41:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,well this just says what I've been saying\Nwe'll go on to the next one
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.03,1:41:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,see what\Nwhat the future could hold for us
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.24,1:41:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in the next slide\Nwhat number is this
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.73,1:41:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,oh\NSo, this is the Louvre. Well, we spoke in Oxford, you know, this last fall, and a few of us went together, a spiritual group,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.57,1:41:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and here's the Louvre, which calibrates at 500, and in the middle is this abomination, this strange glass and aluminum cube.\NThis is magnificent, you know, magnificent, and in the middle is this cube, modernism, calibrates at 180.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.17,1:41:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought it was interesting. Functionally, you can't beat it. Functionally, it's terrific.\NIt just looks really weird there.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.10,1:42:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This is something that was in the A.A. Grapevine back about 1950s, I think.\NIt was originally in the A.A. Grapevine, which was a monthly publication in A.A.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.45,1:42:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It came out of the work of several people, and I think it's such a magnificent way of, in shorthand,\Ndealing with teenagers.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.13,1:42:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Teenagers and adolescents and people, or even children, not to mention your own inner child.\NHere's the tree of self-realization. You see, it's built on the roots of worth, trust, kindness, gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.96,1:42:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all the source of the kundalini energy, which blossoms forth as creativity, purposefulness, health, joy, commitment, fulfillment.\NThat's the tree of self-realization. To say yes to one's potential is to release the kundalini energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.95,1:42:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which then manifests in all these various forms.\NTo say no to it, to say no to it, to say no to it then condemns you to this tree here.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.84,1:43:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-defeating, mistrustful, paranoid, jealous, hateful, fear, guilt, self-pity, drugs and alcohol, crime dependency,\Nall kinds of conflicts. Bad enough it becomes apathy, a feeling of emptiness, alienation,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.72,1:43:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and mental illness.\NSo, it's very simple. I didn't have this when I was working with the girls at Mingus Mountain.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.12,1:43:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But the last lecture I gave there, I finally retired from there, and I've got it meant to bring my watch with me.\NI got one of those watches like you get when you've been with the railroad 20 years. Fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.52,1:43:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You push it, boing, and it tells you the time. It's wonderful. I love it.\NGot my name engraved on the back and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.32,1:43:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I gave a parting lecture, and I had just come across this.\NIt was sent to me by a gentleman that thought we might use it in our work.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.41,1:44:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I thought with teenagers especially, it's very simple to say,\Nlook, which life do you want, you know? You can have this tree or this tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.28,1:44:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It just makes it so clear, diagrammed, and obvious.\NWhich do you want? Drugs and crime, the recidivism, most criminals end up back in prison,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.12,1:44:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or you want a rebirth.\NAnd emerge as a tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.73,1:44:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I like a quick visual like that.\NSo, we, I wanted to get a bunch of them made up for today,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.83,1:44:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because I think some of the people, when they see it, they just want one.\NSo, some of our office staff, Gil, in fact, and Karen, made up.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.03,1:44:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I've got 20. We've got to put 20 of them out in the bookstore.\NAnybody wants them. But I just think it's just a great thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.03,1:44:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, if you blew it up to poster size and do it in color, and the original, this is green.\NThis is green.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.03,1:44:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of very shades of brown.\NI mean, it's just a confrontation with which do you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.76,1:45:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Which do you want? Which do you want?\NAnd it should make it very simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.56,1:45:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people who hate the green tree.\NThey do. They really are.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.28,1:45:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They say no to God, and they hate God.\NAnd, so those who say no, that's your, that's your freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.30,1:45:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom is to say yes or to say no.\NWhen you say no,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.50,1:45:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you cut off the flow of the green tree.\NYou cut off the flow of the Kundalini energy, and the consequences thereof.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.00,1:45:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But, isn't that neat?\NSo, we made 20 of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.10,1:45:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought maybe some of you from out of town.\NWe'll get more made by the next one, and we'll probably put them on the website or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.00,1:45:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I just think, you know, for people doing work with kids, teachers and group therapists with kids and all.\NYeah, this is Ralph.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.70,1:45:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is in the grapevine, 1952 or something.\NCame probably out of the work of Harry Thiebaud.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.90,1:45:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And, who else?\NI forget.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.30,1:46:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But, it's just a beautiful contribution somebody made to us.\NSo, we should take a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.25,1:46:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And, then we'll do, I'll finish a few more things I wanted to say.\NAnd, then we'll have questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.08,1:46:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,As you know, we share, we share the dialogue with people with the audience.\NPeople ask questions, and I answer them, and sign books, and whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.24,1:46:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And, the whole group shares with it.\NIt's sort of fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:24.44,1:46:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You never know what's going to come up.\NSo, we'll take a break, and we'll meet again.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.74,1:46:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll do a grand finale.\NWhat is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.34,1:46:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if there's that great.\NI know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:51.49,1:46:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted you to see that.
